seal     : The strangest victory is the war that never happens. Deterrence is the art of making an attack so costly that no one starts it — of winning by convincing the other side they cannot win. In the nuclear age it became a global, permanent standoff: mutual assured destruction, a peace held in place by the credible promise of annihilation.
